Thanks Margaret.  I&#39;m certainly no electronics wizard.  I&#39;ve built a few small devices and modified others, so this will be a much bigger task.  Just hope I don&#39;t screw it up.  I tend to just jump in the fire and learn as I go.  

I&#39;ve actually had a hack sitting in my bathtub to try for better signal.  Time of day always makes a difference too.  I haven&#39;t kept a detailed log, but I have noticed a difference in reception at different moon phases as well as weather variation.  

The log idea is something I&#39;ve been meaning to start.  Today might be a good time because it&#39;s a new moon.

Jeremy





